The paper discusses the design and analysis of randomized neural networks, which are a type of neural system. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of these networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of randomized neural networks in convolutional filters, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of these networks in structured domains, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
